                    <p>If you prefer a sedan with great mileage and a touch of premium, <span class="font-weight-700">Hyundai Aura</span> with CNG or AMT options is another solid pick.</p>
                    <p><span class="font-weight-700">✅ Top mileage pick:</span> Celerio (CNG/Petrol), Aura (CNG)</p>

                    <h3 class="subheading">🎯 2. Driving Fun & Sporty Feel?</h3>
                    <p>The new-gen <span class="font-weight-700">Maruti Swift</span> continues its legacy as the go-to hatchback for enthusiastic drivers. The 1.2L petrol engine is zippy, the gear shifts are smooth, and the fresh design feels youthful.</p>
                    <p>Looking for something bolder? The <span class="font-weight-700">XUV 3XO's</span> turbo petrol engine delivers punchy performance with a touch of SUV muscle.</p>
                    <p><span class="font-weight-700">✅ Performance picks:</span> Swift (manual or AMT), XUV 3XO (turbo)</p>

                    <h3 class="subheading">🛡️ 3. Prioritize Safety Above All?</h3>
                    <p><span class="font-weight-700">Tata Altroz</span> and <span class="font-weight-700">Tata Nexon</span> are your best bets—both come with 5-star Global NCAP ratings. You also get thick body panels, solid stability at high speeds, and lots of features (like iRA connected tech in Nexon).</p>
                    <p><span class="font-weight-700">Tata Tiago</span> and <span class="font-weight-700">Tata Punch</span> also offer <span class="font-weight-700">6 airbags</span> as standard now, which is unheard of in their price brackets.</p>
                    <p><span class="font-weight-700">✅ Safety first picks:</span> Altroz, Nexon, Punch, Tiago</p>

                    <h3 class="subheading">🏙️ 4. Daily City Commute & Easy Parking?</h3>
                    <p>Compact, efficient, and effortless to park—<span class="font-weight-700">Tiago</span>, <span class="font-weight-700">Swift</span>, and <span class="font-weight-700">Celerio</span> shine in urban scenarios. The clutch-free AMT variants are ideal for bumper-to-bumper traffic. These cars are also easy on the pocket when it comes to running costs and servicing.</p>
                    <p><span class="font-weight-700">✅ City smart picks:</span> Tiago AMT, Swift AMT, Celerio AMT</p>

                    <h3 class="subheading">🚙 5. SUV Styling Under Budget?</h3>
                    <p>Love the commanding stance of an SUV but don't want the size or price tag of one? <span class="font-weight-700">Tata Punch</span>, <span class="font-weight-700">Mahindra XUV 3XO</span>, and <span class="font-weight-700">Maruti Brezza</span> bring that SUV look and practicality under ₹10 lakh. You get high ground clearance, rugged looks, and all the city + weekend functionality.</p>
                    <p><span class="font-weight-700">✅ Mini SUV picks:</span> Punch, XUV 3XO, Brezza</p>

                    <h3 class="subheading">⚡ 6. Want an Electric Option?</h3>
                    <p>Tata Nexon EV's entry-level variants now flirt with the ₹10 lakh range post subsidies (check your state's EV policy). It's India's favorite EV for a reason: real-world range of ~300km, great ride quality, and fast charging options.</p>
                    <p><span class="font-weight-700">✅ Green tech pick:</span> Nexon EV (check specific variants)</p>

